A '''Cart00ney''' or '''Cartooney''' (often spelled with the two zeroes) is an internet [[neologism]] related to an empty and comically overstated threat of legal action.  The derivation of the word is unclear; by some explanations it is simply used as a synonym for "comical" and by others as a [[portmanteau]] of the words [[cartoon]] (alluding to fantasy and exaggeration) and [[attorney]].  The term was originally coined in the [[Usenet]] [[newsgroup]] [[news.admin.net-abuse.email]] and is generally used to mock the presumably fictitious lawyers that the subject threatens to unleash, although the term can also refer to the threats themselves.  The canonical subject is a [[spammer]] reacting to what they consider undeserved censure, such as being publicly identified, blocked, or added to [[blacklist]]s.


